title: Statue of Liberty
content: Iconic National Monument opened in 1886, offering guided tours, a museum & city views.

title: One World Trade Center
content: A casual cafe, a bar with small plates & American fine dining with views from the 101st floor.

title: Empire State Building
content: Iconic, art deco office tower from 1931 with exhibits & observatories on the 86th & 102nd floors.

title: Intrepid Sea, Air & Space Museum
content: Flight museum on an aircraft carrier whose exhibits include a Concorde, submarine & space shuttle.

title: Flatiron Building
content: Architect Daniel Burnham's iconic 1902 triangular tower nicknamed for its clothes iron look.
